		{"id":"f70da6827b41c090","type":"group","x":-1719,"y":-910,"width":2715,"height":1100,"label":"1 Fairy Drain"},
		{"id":"edbab44cca0966cc","type":"group","x":-1719,"y":470,"width":2715,"height":740,"label":"2 Full Moon"},
		{"id":"f5996203dc28e925","type":"group","x":-1719,"y":-2050,"width":2715,"height":720,"label":"0 Physical Restraint"},
		{"id":"a20e252e51951168","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/35_FirstFullMoon/Jane feels at fault.md","x":-2184,"y":-1390,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"dbfe0103158d597e","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/35_FirstFullMoon/Crystal moon shape.md","x":-2255,"y":-677,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"5d0882913438f60d","type":"text","text":"As far as the wolf's perspective, I mean it likes all things shaped like the moon, so it already likes the necklace as soon as it sees it, and thanks to the hug and stuff from her mother it has established that these are pack members, and then later she charges the Crystal and puts it on and gets that effect of being able to communicate with the wolf better, so that's going to really shift things with the wolf. Coming from this sort of negative place of it chafing at being drained all the time, to not being drained and so therefore neutral sort of place, to I guess you could say feeling more supported? Like it's learning that it can trust her I guess, I don't want it to have too much of a long-term thing. Like it doesn't hold grudges, because I don't feel like that's how dogs operate. Not that it can't ever remember anything, but it doesn't continue to throw tantrums and be pissy because it was being drained previously even after it's stopped being drained. I don't know I just feel like my dog usually is just reacting to the situation at hand without having too much of the past or future influencing her mood and stuff, so I want the inner wolf to be like that. I mean maybe it to some degree the werewolf didn't know why it felt bad, it was brand new maybe it was just simply too young to really understand that it was being drained by the fairy just that it didn't feel good and it's needs weren't being met. So that it doesn't really establish a learned association. But anyway, I think the wolf coming into this place where it feels like it can trust her is at least a foundation towards it letting her have control when they are in wolf form. I think I like that idea, it takes control when it feels like it can't trust her. It's just it can only take control while there and we'll form, at least like major control. Not that it can't make her growl or something in human form, but it's easier for the wolf to have control over the actions when they are in wolf form but her consistently meeting its needs and the necklace helping with communication so that she can understand it and what it means like I said is going to establish this sort of trust, the wolf feels safe letting her metaphorically drive when she embraces the wolf and takes care of the wolf. ","x":-2031,"y":-200,"width":400,"height":400},
